---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Usage-Based Pricing - Use Case | PricingNest"
  description="A practical flow for usage-based pricing: estimate unit price from costs and margin, then validate against seat-based alternatives."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Use case: usage-based pricing</h1>
    <p>
      Use this flow to set a per-unit price from unit costs, fixed overhead, and target gross margin, then sanity-check it
      against a seat-based plan.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a class="btn primary" href="/saas-pricing/usage-based-pricing-calculator/">Start with unit pricing</a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="/saas-pricing/use-cases/">All use cases</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <section class="card col8">
      <h2>Recommended steps</h2>
      <ol class="list">
        <li>
          Back into a required unit price:{" "}
          <a href="/saas-pricing/usage-based-pricing-calculator/">usage-based pricing calculator</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          Translate unit pricing into a seat plan comparison:{" "}
          <a href="/saas-pricing/seat-vs-usage-pricing-comparison/">seat vs usage pricing comparison</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          If your product is API-first, convert to a monthly plan price:{" "}
          <a href="/saas-pricing/api-pricing-calculator/">API pricing calculator</a>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Notes</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Model multiple scenarios: average customer vs heavy user (p50 vs p90 usage).</li>
        <li>Separate truly fixed overhead from per-usage vendor costs for cleaner unit economics.</li>
        <li>Use share links to align on assumptions before you pick tiers or minimums.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Good for</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>APIs, events, messages, minutes</li>
        <li>Infra-heavy features</li>
        <li>Products with variable value by usage</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="ad" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Ad slot (optional)</div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

